\pard\f0\fs28   {\b 1. C. nana} (Schultes & Schultes fil.) Boiss. & Heldr. in Boiss.,{\i  Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  2}({\b 13}): 24 (1853). Bulb ovoid. Stem usually 5-10 cm. Leaves 2, as long as stem, 3-5 mm wide, linear, obtuse. Flowers usually solitary; perianth 9-12 mm, whitish, sometimes lilac at apex; tube 2-3 × 2-3 mm; segments elliptic-oblong, obtuse. Filaments c. 2 mm; anthers 3-4 mm. 2n = 18.{\i  Snow-patches,} 1700-2300 {\i m; calcicole. • Mountains of Kriti.} Cr.
