\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 33.    Bellevalia}      Lapeyr.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By V.H. Heywood. 
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Glabrous, bulbous, scapose perennials. Bulbs with a membranous tunic. Leaves several, all basal. Inflorescence a raceme, with numerous white or blue to violet flowers which become brownish, greenish or yellowish after anthesis. Bracts usually small, membranous. Perianth tubular, campanulate or infundibuliform, deeply divided into 6 more or less patent lobes. Stamens 6, inserted at the base of the perianth-lobes; anthers held next to the perianth-segments, blue. Fruit a triquetrous capsule with 3 prominent ribs.
\par

